- - - - - - -
**** WARNING ****
- This feature bypasses many limitations on placing a stucture and therefore should not be used by novices or the general public. If you use this feature on a multiplayer server, I highly suggest limiting it to GM's only.
- Added the "House Plop" ability (something I started working on in 2014 for Kinshi of the Tarkin server. Only took me a year to figure it out! lol...).
- Place a structure, from its deed using a new radial menu option, almost anywhere, with the door rotated to face the direction your character is facing.
- Use the Show Ruler option to extend a green line out from your character to make it easier to see what way you are actually facing.
- It's not a perfect solution, but it does make it much easier to line up player buildings with NPC structures. 





Combat Tatwification!
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = 
NOTE: 
- I am sure most pre-cu SWG fans will hate what I am doing here. Oh well! This project is for me, not them. 
- I don't use Jedi at all, so none of the changes I have made take them into consideration. I did alter their special attacks for consistency/clarity though.

Purpose: 
- LoH is a single player game, so I want to make it such that a person doesn't NEED to multi-box a "healer" just to play the game. 
- To mesh all combat professions with the use Medic 444x rather than said secondary healer.
- To give Health/Action/Mind their own sensible purposes and remove the weirdness that was killing one's self by using special attacks, etc. 

Health: 
- The only stat which will cause incap/death. 
- All attacks can hit it.
- Stimpacks and Quick Heal heal it.
- Tend Damage DOES NOT heal it.
- Does not regen in combat (and extremely slowly out of combat - use Medic!).

Action: 
- Overall 15% chance enemy attacks will damage it.
- All "weapon ability HAM costs" are averaged and applied only to the Action pool. 
- Incap does not occur when it is empty. 
- DoTs still effect it.
- Tend Damage heals it.
- Stimpacks DO NOT heal it.
- Regens more slowly in combat, but very fast when sitting out of combat.

Mind:
- Primary function is to manage healing of Health/Action, and the removal of States/DoTs.
- No enemy can directly attack it.
- DoTs still effect it.
- Incap does not occur when it is empty. 
- Tend Damage, Tend Wound, and Quick Heal all cause Mind wounds (but not Focus/Willpower wounds), with the amount of wounds based on various factors.
- In combat regen was nerfed into the ground (because it is TOTALLY "live forever or until I run out of stimpacks" OVERPOWERED otherwise...), but very fast when sitting out of combat.
- When player lands a good hit he regens 100 Mind.
- Blue Milk still heals mind, until the player's "drink filling" is full. 


src/server/zone/objects/creature/CreatureObjectImplementation.cpp
- - - - - - -
- Health does not regenerate while in combat.
- 50% Action and Mind regen while in combat.
- Action and Mind regen is much higher while sitting when not in combat.
- 15% Action and Mind bonus when kneeling, even in combat.

src/server/zone/managers/combat/CombatManager.cpp
- - - - - - -
- Weapon HAM costs are now only applied to the Action pool. The amount applied is the average of the normal health, action, and mind costs.
- Removed chance to hit Mind with direct attacks. 85% Health, 15% Action
- Removed Mind damage.
- Merged Mind wound application into Action calculations.
- Wounds are increased to primary stats (Health/Action/Mind) when damaged in combat.
- Apply less damage to Mind type armor than Action type, by choosing randomly between them when damage is applied to Action pool.
- Added a "Shocked Rally" Mind heal, based on available Action, when the player is hit for more than 25% of their Health in a single hit. Min of 500 health required to get this "kick in the pants"!

src/server/zone/managers/player/PlayerManagerImplementation.cpp
- - - - - - -
- Wounds are always applied when cloning. Random amount higher than default SWG, but less if you clone where your data is stored.
- Insured items decay at 3% rather than 1%. Uninsured still decay at 5%.
- Incapacitation and death only occur if the player is out of Health.

src/server/zone/objects/creature/commands/HealDamageCommand.h
- Stimpacks are now only for healing Health.
- Set amount of Action healed to 1 regardless of stimpack power, player skill, etc.
- Mind cost based on Focus and Injury Treatment skill.
 
src/server/zone/objects/creature/commands/TendDamageCommand.h
- - - - - - -
- Tend Damage is now the primary way to heal Action,
- Mind cost based on Focus and Injury Treatment skill.
- Reduced wounds.

src/server/zone/objects/creature/commands/TendWoundCommand.h
- - - - - - -
- Mind cost based on Focus and Injury Treatment skill.
- Increase wounds.
 
src/server/zone/objects/creature/commands/TendCommand.h
- - - - - - -
- TendDamage heals Action based more on player skill and with an additional crit chance, but only heals 1 Health.
- Both TendDamage and TendWound only cause Mind wounds, no longer wounds Focus and Willpower. 

src/server/zone/objects/creature/commands/QuickHealCommand.h
- - - - - - -
- Made this into an "Oh Shit" self heal button that can now be used in combat.
- Still heals both Health and Action.
- Increased min possible healing to 400. Max is 400 + random(350 + Injury Treatment Skill).
- Mind cost based on Focus and Injury Treatment skill.
- Increased Mind wounds to healed amount / 20, but no longer wounds Focus and Willpower.

src/server/zone/objects/creature/commands/HealStateCommand.h
- - - - - - -
- Mind cost based on Focus and Injury Treatment skill.

