Junk Dealers: Better Prices for Crafted Items!
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = 
src/server/zone/managers/crafting/CraftingManager.idl
src/server/zone/managers/crafting/CraftingManagerImplementation.cpp
src/server/zone/managers/crafting/labratories/SharedLabratory.cpp
src/server/zone/managers/crafting/labratories/SharedLabratory.h
src/server/zone/objects/player/sessions/crafting/CraftingSessionImplementation.cpp
- - - - - - -
- Dramatically improved the Junk Dealer values!
- Complexity is no longer used as it is too arbitrary, thus experimentation is not required to get a good price.
- Price is now based up on units of resources used (in the final combination), resource quality, player skill, and a bit of luck.
- Subcomponents are taken into account, but based only upon an estimate of their resource quantity.
- Optional component slots that are empty are ignored, ya cheeky pirates!
- Player skill is capped at 120, because every profession can hit it (and Shipwright Engines +17 is too good of a bonus).
- Max price is capped around 35,000 credits, "in a perfect world".
- Explore the math if you want to ruin the mystery of it all :)




